    "markdown": "## MRI Knee Without Contrast Overview\n\n### What the scan assesses\nAn MRI Knee Without Contrast evaluates:\n- Ligaments (ACL, PCL, MCL, LCL)\n- Menisci (medial and lateral)\n- Articular cartilage\n- Bone marrow\n- Joint fluid and swelling\n### Why choose non-contrast imaging\n- No risk of gadolinium side effects\n- Shorter visit time\n- Lower cost than contrast studies\n- Ideal for most sports injuries and chronic pain\n\n## Risks & Limitations of the MRI Knee Without Contrast\n\n- \\*\\*Limitations in detecting subtle inflammation\\*\\* – contrast may be needed for very early synovitis.\n- \\*\\*Metal implant contraindications\\*\\* – pacemakers, cochlear implants, or older aneurysm clips may disqualify you.\n- \\*\\*Claustrophobia considerations\\*\\* – open MRI or mild sedation can help.\n\n## List of Parameters Considered During the MRI Knee Without Contrast\n\n- \\*\\*ACL & PCL integrity\\*\\* – tears, sprains, or avulsions\n- \\*\\*Medial & lateral menisci\\*\\* – bucket-handle, radial, or complex tears\n- \\*\\*Articular cartilage\\*\\* – thinning, fissures, or defects\n- \\*\\*Bone marrow edema\\*\\* – bruises, stress reactions\n- \\*\\*Synovial fluid\\*\\* – joint effusion or bleeding\n\n## When to Take Test\n\n1. \\*\\*Accurate diagnosis without dye risks\\*\\* – see the injury clearly.\n2. \\*\\*Monitoring healing progress\\*\\* – track ligament or cartilage recovery.\n3. \\*\\*Pre-surgical planning\\*\\* – surgeons use images to map the repair.\n\n## Benefits of Taking the Test\n\n- \\*\\*No gadolinium-related side effects\\*\\* – no injection, no rare allergic reactions.\n- \\*\\*Shorter scan time\\*\\* – in and out in under 30 minutes.\n- \\*\\*Cost-effective\\*\\* – pay only for the scan you need.\n\n## Illnesses Diagnosed with MRI Knee Without Contrast\n\n- \\*\\*Ligament sprains & tears\\*\\* – ACL, PCL, MCL, LCL injuries\n- \\*\\*Meniscal tears\\*\\* – medial or lateral\n- \\*\\*Osteoarthritis\\*\\* – cartilage loss, bone spurs\n- \\*\\*Bone bruises\\*\\* – after trauma or sports impact\n\n## Preparing for MRI Knee Without Contrast\n\n### Instructions\n- Wear loose, metal-free clothing.\n- Remove jewelry, watches, and hairpins.\n- Inform staff of implants or pacemakers.\n### Prerequisites\n- Doctor’s referral (can be arranged on-site).\n- Recent X-ray may be requested if fracture is suspected.\n### Eligibility\n- Pregnant patients: generally safe after first trimester.\n- Young children may need mild sedation; discuss with our team.\n### Procedure for Taking the Test\n1. Check-in at Cadabams Diagnostics reception.\n2. Change into provided gown.\n3. Lie on the MRI table; knee positioned in a comfortable coil.\n4. Hold still for 20–30 minutes while the machine scans.\n5. Collect belongings and leave immediately—no recovery time needed.\n### Caution Before Taking the Test\n- Notify if you have:\n- Pacemaker\n- Cochlear implant\n- Orthopedic screws/plates (most are safe)\n- History of claustrophobia"
